    money: "Rising estrogen is likely giving you the urge to splurge on products and services that help you have fun (such as video games, roller blades or art supplies) or improve your appearance (like a trip to the hair salon, cosmetics or jewelry). You may also end up spending more than you intended during high-energy events — like a big sale, home party or charity auction — because high estrogen gets you more easily swept up by the excitement. Fortunately, this same hormone that seems to encourage you to spend, spend, spend can also help you tighten your purse strings. The trick is to have a clear-cut savings goal in mind, for instance, to save a certain amount to buy a car. Then, when you're considering parting with your cash for something you don't need, think about this goal. When you remind yourself that you want to save for a specific purpose, high estrogen helps strengthen your resolve to reach it, making it easier to put down your wallet and step away from the cash register.",
