    food: "When choosing meals, snacks and beverages, you could be drawn to those that seem fun to eat (such as a food that's a miniature-sized version of its original) or that have bold, complex or nontraditional flavors (such as a green tea and basil combo). That's a side effect of high estrogen, which inspires you to seek out more interesting experiences and stretch your cuisine comfort zone. Been meaning to change your eating style, for instance, eliminating foods with a certain ingredient? When estrogen is on the rise like it is today, you'll find it easier to turn down foods you no longer want to consume since this hormone helps strengthen your commitment to important goals.",
