    romance: "\"If you're single If you're seeking a partner, your confidence and optimism about finding one climbs along with your estrogen level. So, you may put more effort into your search — for instance, by joining a networking group or exercise class — since you're more hopeful it could pay off with a love connection. Regardless of whether you're actively looking for love or you're committed to staying single, you'll still find it difficult to resist fantasizing about what it would be like to go on hot dates with some of the folks you come in contact with today. And the stars of your romantic daydreams will likely be physically attractive, in a position of power or are filled with confidence since that's the type of person high estrogen is pushing you toward in Week 2 of your cycle. If you're in a relationship As your estrogen rises, you're more optimistic about your relationship, where you're headed, how long you'll be together and how strong a couple you two make. However, at this point in your cycle, you may also be sneaking peeks at other cuties around you. Don't take this urge to look as an indication of whether there are cracks in your relationship. It's just high estrogen pushing you to take one final glimpse into the dating pool to make sure you haven't missed out on someone who might be a better genetic match-up for your adorable ovum that will make an appearance at ovulation. This hormone doesn't seem to care that the mate you already have is a total cutie, makes a mean cappuccino and always gives you control over the TV remote.\"",
    sex: "High hormones are doing all they can to help you enjoy sexual fun: They're prompting more powerful reward sensations in the brain from physical touch; they're boosting lubrication, which helps make sexual play more comfortable; and, they're making orgasms easier to attain and more pleasurable. With estrogen so high, you're also craving novelty and adventure. As a result, you may be getting tired of the same-old thing in your bedroom — whether it's a position, video, toy or fantasy — and want to try something new.",
    career: "You could be inspired to wake up early, stay up late and skip meals and other necessities to complete a task you enjoy as high estrogen revs your desire to do, do, do! This means you can make some serious headway on a task when you set your mind to it. Stuck working on a task you're not passionate about? Then your biggest challenge is keeping interruptions to a minimum since this same elevated hormone can make you more easily lured away from your work by anything remotely interesting, like texting a friend or watching funny pet videos. With high estrogen revving your mental and physical skills, you're happiest when working on anything you find challenging and requires you to plumb the depths of your abilities.",
    food: "You're more easily persuaded to try new dishes and may take samples from everyone else's plates to get a taste of the foods you didn't choose. Pals with bites taken out of their lunch can blame your high estrogen for your culinary curiosity. As this hormone rises, it makes you more adventurous in all areas, including what you eat. This hormone is further egging you on to try a variety of edibles by enhancing your taste buds' flavor-detecting abilities and giving you a more intensely rewarding feeling when you consume food you find pleasurable. Despite your desire to try different foods, you'll probably find it's still easier to adhere to a specific eating plan you've adopted, such as consuming more whole grains or fewer highly-processed items. That's because as estrogen rises, it helps you muster the willpower to stick to good-for-you goals.",
