    energy: "So long as you're not being dragged down by an energy-robber (such as an overly-large meal or major stress), you'll likely be experiencing an unmistakable whoosh of mental and physical energy that lasts all day long. That's what happens when estrogen reaches the heights it does today: It gives you the kind of zip that makes a speed skater envious. Unfortunately, for some women, this high hormone energy rush can also lead to anxiety or feeling on-edge. If this happens to you, try reining in antsiness with a calming technique, such as self-massage, yoga or meditation.",
    money: "You could get the urge to spend more — especially on luxury products or high-priced services — as high-and-rising estrogen revs everything that prompts you to splurge: You're in a better mood, which makes shopping more fun; you're more easily excited, say, by fast-talking salespeople or spendthrift friends, who goad you to empty your wallet; and, you've got heaping doses of hopefulness coursing through you, making you absolutely certain that you'll be able to somehow afford the expenditures no matter what the price tag. To keep from blowing your life savings on a yacht, mansion or tennis bracelet, remind yourself of an important savings goal — for instance, getting an advanced degree or starting a family — whenever you're about to splash out on an unnecessary purchase. The same hormone that pushes you to spend can also have the opposite effect: It can ratchet up your resolve to squirrel away cash when you have a specific savings plan you want to achieve.",
    romance: "\"If you're single An intense craving to make a love connection due to super-high estrogen can push you to step out of your comfort zone and try a new activity as a way to find someone new, for instance, maybe you decide to go dancing even though you have two left feet or you finally agree to a blind date set-up your Aunt Sally has been bugging you about for months. No matter where you end up looking for love, keep in mind that the closer you get to ovulation, the more high estrogen pushes you toward short-term mate material — someone who's ambitious, confident, flirtatious and physically attractive — over someone with more long-term potential — which would generally be someone who's cooperative, funny, warm and caring. Now, this doesn't mean you have to follow what your hormones have to say about who you end up with. In fact, being aware of what sneaky little tricks your hormones are up to in the love department can actually help you by giving you the power to override their influences. This way, you can pick the person who is truly right for you. If you're in a relationship If all is well in your relationship, then high estrogen is making it even better: You'll be doling out more affection, planning romantic dates and overlooking any of your partner's missteps. And, your honey doesn't have to do a lot to win your affections: You're easily bowled over by unexpected romantic gestures thanks to high estrogen that amps up both a desire to connect with your cutie and a love of surprises. Yet, strangely, no matter how close you feel to your sugarpie, you'll still likely be scanning streets, stores and crowds for other hotties. It's most likely not an indication of a weakness in your relationship, but rather simply a side effect of high estrogen, which makes you want to take another look around to see if there's another suitable suitor for your egg to partner up with at ovulation.\"",
    sex: "Thanks to high hormones, you'll be experiencing many libidinous urges today. Give in to them and there's a big chance you won't be disappointed. That's because you're closing in on ovulation day, which means you have greater sensitivity to sensual touch, you're more easily aroused, your body is producing plenty of comfort-boosting lubrication and climaxes are so right there for the taking. And once you achieve one, its intensity can have you seriously wondering if you broke something. But, in a good way.",
    career: "High estrogen is charging up your confidence, so you may be itching to ask for something big from a supervisor, teacher or other person who can help make your dreams come true. Or, you might take some kind of risk to propel a goal forward, such as asking for flex-time so you can start a side business or changing college majors. You're enjoying lots of Week 2 super-high brainpower, energy, verbal skills, extroversion, creativity and competitiveness. So, jump on tasks that require these kinds of abilities since you'll excel at them with less effort.",
    food: "You may be drawn toward lighter foods today, such as salads, broth-based soups or wraps. Or you may eat a snack on the run rather than eat full meals. That's because high estrogen is reining in your appetite slightly, making heavier meals less appetizing. When you do get the urge to chow down, you'll probably crave a dish that's spicy, is made up of an eclectic variety of ingredients, is a special delicacy or is different from what you normally choose. When estrogen is high, it encourages you to be more adventurous with your palate. When trying to adhere to a specific eating style or meal plan you've committed to, you'll find it's a tad easier to choose only the foods you want to eat and shun the ones you want to avoid. You can thank rising estrogen, which reinforces your resolve to stay the course.",
    sleep: "If all else is going well — for example, you haven't overdone it on caffeine and you're not aching from overexerting yourself at the gym — then high estrogen is helping you get some seriously high-quality zzz's. That is, after you rein in any hormone-fueled brain-buzzing jibber-jabber that's going on in your head as you try to drift off.",
