    sex: "The general rule of thumb is that the higher your hormones climb, the more intense your sex drive gets and the more fulfilling your climaxes become. With that in mind, your hormones are pretty darned high today. If you take the time to enjoy sexual fun solo or with a partner, you can expect more tingles from every touch, a higher production of lubrication, which helps make passion-play more comfortable, and greater ease in reaching those wonderfully fulfilling orgasms. Whether you're happily hitched or prefer the solo life, the kind of sexual partner you're fantasizing about most during your Week 2 tends to be assertive, gruff and rough around the edges. Basically, the total opposite of what lights your fire during other weeks of your cycle. The reason Mother Nature pushes you toward this type is because these traits denote a higher amount of testosterone, which ups your odds of a healthier genetic match-up in case you get pregnant during ovulation. You don't even have to be trying to get pregnant, have pregnancy plans anywhere on the horizon or want to get pregnant ever — yet, your biological urges will still point you toward this type of person every Week 2 just in case.",
