    money: "Today can be a spend it or save it kind of day — all because of high estrogen. If you go into the world armed with your cash and credit cards, chances are you're going to blow a lot of it as this hormone amps up your desire for fun, excitement and products that boost your personal power and beauty. However, if you go into the world leaving your cash and credit cards at home and arming yourself with a note that reminds you of an important financial goal you want to reach — such as socking away enough money for a down payment on a house — then this hormone will help you save by bolstering your willpower so you can resist temptation.",
    romance: "\"If you're single You may find it a bit easier today to win over cuties you're attracted to. That's because you've got a lot of study-proven high-estrogen benefits on your side: You're more charming and confident; your facial features and voice undergo subtle changes that make you more attractive; you're walking and dancing in ways that make your movements more alluring; and, your body is pumping out more pheromones — scentless chemicals in your sweat that make potential mates more captivated by you. If you're in a relationship You're more confident and hopeful about your honey. Even if friends or family think you could do better, you're optimistic that with a few minor tweaks, you can have the mate and relationship you've always hoped for.\"",
    sex: "Your desire for sexual fun is on the high end of its scale as high hormones push your libido into gotta-have-it-now territory. Whether you take a long break for passion or sneak in a quickie for a solo jaunt or playtime with a partner, you're going to probably consider it one of the highlights of your day. That's because your hormones are helping you achieve some of the more memorable and satisfying orgasms of your entire cycle by escalating the amount of physical sensation you experience.",
    career: "You could have a \"Eureka!\" moment today where you come up with an ingenious plan or perfect solution to a problem at work, school or on a project. That's high estrogen's doing. As the level of this hormone soars, it helps your brain churn out more creative ideas. Spiking estrogen makes you more comfortable being the center of attention. So, find a reason to grab the spotlight today, for instance, by hosting an impromptu event or leading a meeting.",
    food: "You'll probably realize at some point that you can go longer without eating or you can eat less and not feel hungry, which is a side effect of high estrogen. While you may find this is a handy trick if you're channeling all your high-hormone energy into a jam-packed to-do list and have no time for chowing down, it's still key to consume full, healthy meals throughout the day — no matter how long you can go without eating before hunger pangs kick in — because it helps keep your blood sugar stable, your metabolism high and your energy from dipping. If you're on a specific diet, then you'll probably realize it's been easier to avoid eating anything on your foods-to-ditch list. That's a result of high estrogen, which bolsters your resolve to meet good-for-you goals.",
    sleep: "At some point in the middle of your day when you're speeding through the office or school halls, zooming around town and whirling dervishing your way through social events, you may wonder if you'll ever get to sleep considering all the high-flying energy you have. Rest assured, the same high estrogen that revs your daytime pep helps you get better sleep at night, too.",
