    romance: "\"If you're single Even if you don't consciously realize it, you're likely putting more time and effort into your appearance and wearing clothing or accessories that make you feel like a million bucks. That's high estrogen's influence. When this hormone gets near its peak, it motivates you to doll yourself up to attract a mate and it pushes you toward high-priced and designer goods as a way to ward off potential romantic rivals who might be competing for the hottie you're interested in. If you're in a relationship Good luck to your sweetheart today: You're likely going to be talking his or her ear off! That's what happens when estrogen gets as high as it does today — it makes you want to chat like it's your job. And since this high hormone also makes you enjoy being around your mate more, she or he is the one you'll want to shower with all your deepest secrets, fondest desires, wittiest observations and, well, just about anything else that happens to enter your thoughts.\"",
    sex: "Week 2 is when many aspects of your body and brain peak. And, your libido and force of your orgasms is definitely on that list. As long as you're not facing any sex-quashing challenges — for instance, lack of sleep or a recent injury — then you're probably going to want to take full advantage of today's peaking sex drive and powerful climaxes. And, if you don't, chances are, you could be driven to distraction with endless X-rated daydreams until you do.",
    career: "You may astound co-workers, school chums, bandmates and other folks around you with the larger number of contributions you make today. For instance, you might propose a new way to improve the company's bottom line, pitch in on a big task even though your workload is already overflowing, pipe up a lot more in class, volunteer to lead a science project or come up with a whole set of new songs for your band to play. That's high estrogen for you: It's making you more energized and motivated, giving you the momentum to do a lot more. Rising estrogen gives you the urge to travel, so you might jump on any opportunity to run errands, get supplies or hop on a plane to visit a client in person.",
    food: "Compared to your eating habits in the second half of your cycle, high estrogen has you eating smaller portions and fewer snacks and gravitating toward more nutritious foods. You're also more adventurous, willing to try a dish even if you're not sure what's in it. Your willingness to take an eating risk can pay off big today, however, because spiking estrogen is sharpening your taste buds and sense of smell, making foods you enjoy taste even more delicious. As estrogen rises high, it revs your self-control, so if you have an eating plan you've been wanting to try or one you need help following, this hormone can help you pick the right foods and avoid the wrong ones.",
